"self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "plain.sessions.backends.base.SessionBase.get_expiry_age", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Get the number of seconds until the session expires.\n\nOptionally, this function accepts `modification` and `expiry` keyword\narguments specifying the modification and expiry of the session."]}, {"name": "plain.sessions.backends.base.SessionBase.get_expiry_date", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Get session the expiry date (as a datetime object).\n\nOptionally, this function accepts `modification` and `expiry` keyword\narguments specifying the modification and expiry of the session."]}, {"name": "plain.sessions.backends.base.SessionBase.set_expiry", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "value", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Set a custom expiration for the session. `value` can be an integer,\na Python `datetime` or `timedelta` object or `None`.\n\nIf `value` is an integer, the session will expire after that many\nseconds of inactivity. If set to `0` then the session will expire on\nbrowser close.\n\nIf `value` is a `datetime` or `timedelta` object, the session\nwill expire at that specific future time.\n\nIf `value` is `None`, the session uses the global session expiry\npolicy.\n"]}, {"name": "plain.sessions.backends.base.SessionBase.get_expire_at_browser_close", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Return `True` if the session is set to expire when the browser\ncloses, and `False` if there's an expiry date. Use\n`get_expiry_date()` or `get_expiry_age()` to find the actual expiry\ndate/age, if there is one.\n"]}, {"name": "plain.sessions.backends.base.SessionBase.flush", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Remove the current session data from the database and regenerate the\nkey."]}, {"name": "plain.sessions.backends.base.SessionBase.cycle_key", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Create a new session key, while retaining the current session data."]}, {"name": "plain.sessions.backends.base.SessionBase.exists", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "session_key", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Return True if the given session_key already exists.", "Methods that child classes must implement."]}, {"name": "plain.sessions.backends.base.SessionBase.create", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Create a new session instance. Guaranteed to create a new object with\na unique key and will have saved the result once (with empty data)\nbefore the method returns."]}, {"name": "plain.sessions.backends.base.SessionBase.save", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "must_create", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Save the session data. If 'must_create' is True, create a new session\nobject (or raise CreateError). Otherwise, only update an existing\nobject and don't create one (raise UpdateError if needed)."]}, {"name": "plain.sessions.backends.base.SessionBase.delete", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "session_key", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Delete the session data under this key. If the key